29/11/2002
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The Croatian mission for Afghanistan staged a short demonstration of their skills in Zagreb on Thursday (28 November). The mission, composed of 44 police officers including four women, will join the UN mission in Afghanistan for three months next year and will be allowed to carry arms. Shortly before the demonstration, Deputy Defence Minister Zlatko Gareljic met with members of the parliamentary panels for national security and foreign affairs to discuss Croatia's contributions to UN operations in Afghanistan. (HINA - 28/11/02)
